{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-post-detail-js","path":"/post/how-to-combine-javascript-files-in-magento-2/","result":{"data":{"wpPost":{"title":"How to Combine Javascript files in Magento 2","content":"\n<p>Combining Javascript files is a widely adopted practice to speed up page loading by reducing the number of HTTP requests required to bring Javascripts to your pages.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>By having all JS files combined, you only need to load one combined file instead of multiple separate javascript modules.</p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong><em>How to combine Javascript files in Magento 2:</em></strong> There are two methods to combine Javascript modules.</p>\n\n\n\n<h1 class=\"wp-block-heading\">How to Combine Javascript Files in Magento 2: A Comprehensive Guide</h1>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Merging Javascripts</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Simplifying the Combination of JS Files in Magento 2: The Merging Technique</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><div data-gatsby-image-wrapper=\"\" style=\"position:relative;overflow:hidden;display:inline-block;vertical-align:top\" class=\"gatsby-image-wrapper gatsby-image-wrapper-constrained wp-image-1204 inline-gatsby-image-wrapper\"><div style=\"max-width:1024px;display:block\"><img alt=\"\" role=\"presentation\" aria-hidden=\"true\" src=\"data:image/svg+xml;charset=utf-8,%3Csvg%20height=&#x27;608&#x27;%20width=&#x27;1024&#x27;%20xmlns=&#x27;http://www.w3.org/2000/svg&#x27;%20version=&#x27;1.1&#x27;%3E%3C/svg%3E\" style=\"max-width:100%;display:block;position:static\"/></div><div aria-hidden=\"true\" data-placeholder-image=\"\" style=\"height:100%;left:0;position:absolute;top:0;width:100%\"></div><img data-gatsby-image-ssr=\"\" data-wp-inline-image=\"1\" data-main-image=\"\" style=\"height:100%;left:0;position:absolute;top:0;transform:translateZ(0);transition:opacity 250ms linear;width:100%;will-change:opacity;opacity:0\" sizes=\"(min-width: 1024px) 1024px, 100vw\" decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" data-s