f434/8585799e9b8d5b0115949883a5e26110/How-to-Combine-Javascript-files-in-Magento-2-01-1.png?u=https%3A%2F%2Fwebguru.dev%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F03%2FHow-to-Combine-Javascript-files-in-Magento-2-01-1.png&a=w%3D256%26h%3D152%26fm%3Dpng%26q%3D90&cd=2023-03-10T04%3A38%3A39\",\"srcSet\":\"/_gatsby/image/85c91041f2b7faae4042dcaa473bf434/8585799e9b8d5b0115949883a5e26110/How-to-Combine-Javascript-files-in-Magento-2-01-1.png?u=https%3A%2F%2Fwebguru.dev%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F03%2FHow-to-Combine-Javascript-files-in-Magento-2-01-1.png&a=w%3D256%26h%3D152%26fm%3Dpng%26q%3D90&cd=2023-03-10T04%3A38%3A39 256w,/_gatsby/image/85c91041f2b7faae4042dcaa473bf434/aeaa2fe36626c9c2c6f6cba2b442d731/How-to-Combine-Javascript-files-in-Magento-2-01-1.png?u=https%3A%2F%2Fwebguru.dev%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F03%2FHow-to-Combine-Javascript-files-in-Magento-2-01-1.png&a=w%3D512%26h%3D304%26fm%3Dpng%26q%3D90&cd=2023-03-10T04%3A38%3A39 512w,/_gatsby/image/85c91041f2b7faae4042dcaa473bf434/ab2420b5a5bff5c8993b95f47e6231c5/How-to-Combine-Javascript-files-in-Magento-2-01-1.png?u=https%3A%2F%2Fwebguru.dev%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F03%2FHow-to-Combine-Javascript-files-in-Magento-2-01-1.png&a=w%3D1024%26h%3D608%26fm%3Dpng%26q%3D90&cd=2023-03-10T04%3A38%3A39 1024w\",\"sizes\":\"(min-width: 1024px) 1024px, 100vw\"}},\"layout\":\"constrained\",\"width\":1024,\"height\":608},\"alt\":\"How to Combine Javascript files in Magento 2 01\",\"className\":\"wp-image-1204 inline-gatsby-image-wrapper\",\"data-wp-inline-image\":\"1\"}</script></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The easiest way to combine all your JS files is by using the merging technique, which combines all the files into one large file. Here&#8217;s how to do it:</p>\n\n\n\n<p>1.Log into the Magento 2 Backend and go to Stores → Configuration → Advanced → Developer.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>2. Switch to the desired Storeview using the switcher on the top ribbon, if necessary. Merging can be enabled separately for each store.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>3. Expand the Javascript Settings section and enable the option to Merge JavaScript Files.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>4. If you want to make the combined JS file smaller, enable the option to Minify JavaScript Files. This will make Magento 2 remove formatting, spacing, and other non-significant parts of the combined scripts.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>5. Go to System → Cache Management, scroll to the Advanced Cache Management section, and press the Flush Javascript/CSS Cache button.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>6. Then, consecutively press the Flush Magento Cache and Flush Cache Storage buttons on the top ribbon.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>7. Regenerate the static content using the Flush Static Files Cache button in the Advanced Cache Management section.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>This will result in all Javascript on all pages being combined into one large file. However, this may not be enough. Merging only combines files loaded via layouts, i.e., files that are present on every page. For on-demand Javascript loaded via the internal Magento 2 RequireJS engine, you need to use bunding as well. Before performing these steps, it is important to <a href=\"/how-to-enable-magento-2-developer-mode/\">enable Magento 2 developer mode</a>.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Bundling Javascript</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Combining On-Demand JS Files in Magento 2: The Bundling Technique</p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong><em>Magento 2 Javascript bundling</em></strong> is an important aspect of optimizing website performance. By combining Javascript files, you can reduce the number of HTTP requests and improve page loading speed. However, it&#8217;s essential to understand how Javascript bundling works in Magento 2, particularly in the context of the RequireJS engine. RequireJS is a modern JS loading engine that allows developers to restrict JS files to only load on specific pages. As a result, if you merge all your JS files into one combined file, it may not actually improve your website&#8217;s performance because RequireJS loads the files asynchronously, only when they are needed. Understanding the intricacies of <strong><em>Javascript bundling in Magento 2</em></strong> is crucial for ensuring that your website performs optimally. In this article, we&#8217;ll explore <strong><em>how to combine Javascript files in Magento 2</em></strong> while taking into account the role of RequireJS.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><div data-gatsby-image-wrapper=\"\" style=\"position:relative;overflow:hidden;display:inline-block;vertical-align:top\" class=\"gatsby-image-wrapper gatsby-image-wrapper-constrained wp-image-1205 inline-gatsby-image-wrapper\"><div style=\"max-width:678px;display:block\"><img alt=\"\" role=\"presentation\" aria-hidden=\"true\" src=\"data:image/svg+xml;charset=utf-8,%3Csvg%20height=&#x27;212&#x27;%20width=&#x27;678&#x27;%20xmlns=&#x27;http://www.w3.org/2000/svg&#x27;%20version=&#x27;1.1&#x27;%3E%3C/svg%3E\" style=\"max-width:100%;display:block;position:static\"/></div><div aria-hidden=\"true\" data-placeholder-image=\"\" style=\"height:100%;left:0;position:absolute;top:0;width:100%\"></div><img data-gatsby-image-ssr=\"\" data-wp-inline-image=\"2\" data-main-image=\"\" style=\"height:100%;left:0;position:absolute;top:0;transform:translateZ(0);transition:opacity 250ms linear;width:100%;will-change:opacity;opacity:0\" sizes=\"(min-width: 678px) 678px, 100vw\" decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" data-src=\"/_gatsby/image/ee1800e39e88e194507dc0911c53faab/c62576f1f0546965847c477a0b839063/How-to-Combine-Javascript-files-in-Magento-2-02.png?u=https%3A%2F%2Fwebguru.dev%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F03%2FHow-to-Combine-Javascript-files-in-Magento-2-02.png&amp;a=w%3D170%26h%3D53%26fm%3Dpng%26q%3D90&amp;cd=2023-03-10T04%3A43%3A30\" data-srcset=\"/_gatsby/image/ee1800e39e88e194507dc0911c53faab/c62576f1f0546965847c477a0b839063/How-to-Combine-Javascript-files-in-Magento-2-02.png?u=https%3A%2F%2Fwebguru.dev%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F03%2FHow-to-Combine-Javascript-files-in-Magento-2-02.png&amp;a=w%3D170%26h%3D53%26fm%3Dpng%26q%3D90&amp;cd=2023-03-10T04%3A43%3A30 170w,/_gatsby/image/ee1800e39e88e194507dc0911c53faab/b2492daa83e9da8389f5d26273d1d994/How-to-Combine-Javascript-files-in-Magento-2-02.png?u=https%3A%2F%2Fwebguru.dev%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F03%2FHow-to-Combine-Javascript-files-in-Magento-2-02.png&amp;a=w%3D339%26h%3D106%26fm%3Dpng%26q%3D90&amp;cd=2023-03-10T04%3A43%3A30 339w,/_gatsby/image/ee1800e39e88e194507dc0911c53faab/21b33590a7bc7881a609788ba56181c3/How-to-Combine-Javascript-files-in-Magento-2-02.png?u=https%3A%2F%2Fwebguru.dev%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F03%2FHow-to-Combine-Javascript-files-in-Magento-2-02.png&amp;a=w%3D678%26h%3D212%26fm%3Dpng%26q%3D90&amp;cd=2023-03-10T04%3A43%3A30 678w\" alt=\"\"/><noscript><img data-gatsby-image-ssr=\"\" data-wp-inline-image=\"2\" data-main-image=\"\" style=\"height:100%;left:0;position:absolute;top:0;transform:translateZ(0);transition:opacity 250ms linear;width:100%;will-change:opacity;opacity:0\" sizes=\"(min-width: 678px) 678px, 100vw\" decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" src=\"/_gatsby/image/ee1800e39e88e194507dc0911c53faab/c62576f1f0546965847c477a0b839063/How-to-Combine-Javascript-files-in-Magento-2-02.png?u=https%3A%2F%2Fwebguru.dev%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F03%2FHow-to-Combine-Javascript-files-in-Magento-2-02.png&amp;a=w%3D170%26h%3D53%26fm%3Dpng%26q%3D90&amp;cd=2023-03-10T04%3A43%3A30\" srcSet=\"/_gatsby/image/ee1800e39e88e194507dc0911c53faab/c62576f1f0546965847c477a0b839063/How-to-Combine-Javascript-files-in-Magento-2-02.png?u=https%3A%2F%2Fwebguru.dev%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F03%2FHow-to-Combine-Javascript-files-in-Magento-2-02.png&amp;a=w%3D170%26h%3D53%26fm%3Dpng%26q%3D90&amp;cd=2023-03-10T04%3A43%3A30 170w,/_gatsby/image/ee1800e39e88e194507dc0911c53faab/b2492daa83e9da8389f5d26273d1d994/How-to-Combine-Javascript-files-in-Magento-2-02.png?u=https%3A%2F%2Fwebguru.dev%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F03%2FHow-to-Combine-Javascript-files-in-Magento-2-02.png&amp;a=w%3D339%26h%3D106%26fm%3Dpng%26q%3D90&amp;cd=2023-03-10T04%3A43%3A30 339w,/_gatsby/image/ee1800e39e88e194507dc0911c53faab/21b33590a7bc7881a609788ba56181c3/How-to-Combine-Javascript-files-in-Magento-2-02.png?u=https%3A%2F%2Fwebguru.dev%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F03%2FHow-to-Combine-Javascript-files-in-Magento-2-02.png&amp;a=w%3D678%26h%3D212%26fm%3Dpng%26q%3D90&amp;cd=2023-03-10T04%3A43%3A30 678w\" alt=\"\"/></noscript><script type=\"module\">const t=\"undefined\"!=typeof HTMLImageElement&&\"loading\"in HTMLImageElement.prototype;if(t){const t=document.querySelectorAll(\"img[data-main-image]\");for(let e of t){e.dataset.src&&(e.setAttribute(\"src\",e.dataset.src),e.removeAttribute(\"data-src\")),e.dataset.srcset&&(e.setAttribute(\"srcset\",e.dataset.srcset),e.removeAttribute(\"data-srcset\"));const t=e.parentNode.querySelectorAll(\"source[data-srcset]\");for(let e of t)e.setAttribute(\"srcset\",e.dataset.srcset),e.removeAttribute(\"data-srcset\");e.complete&&(e.style.opacity=1,e.parentNode.parentNode.querySelector(\"[data-placeholder-image]\").style.opacity=0)}}</script></div><script type=\"application/json\" data-wp-inline-image-hydration=\"2\">{\"image\":{\"images\":{\"sources\":[],\"fallback\":{\"src\":\"/_gatsby/image/ee1800e39e88e194507dc0911c53faab/c62576f1f0546965847c477a0b839063/How-to-Combine-Javascript-files-in-Magento-2-02.png?u=https%3A%2F%2Fwebguru.dev%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F03%2FHow-to-Combine-Javascript-files-in-Magento-2-02.png&a=w%3D170%26h%3D53%26fm%3Dpng%26q%3D90&cd=2023-03-10T04%3A43%3A30\",\"srcSet\":\"/_gatsby/image/ee1800e39e88e194507dc0911c53faab/c62576f1f0546965847c477a0b839063/How-to-Combine-Javascript-files-in-Magento-2-02.png?u=https%3A%2F%2Fwebguru.dev%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F03%2FHow-to-Combine-Javascript-files-in-Magento-2-02.png&a=w%3D170%26h%3D53%26fm%3Dpng%26q%3D90&cd=2023-03-10T04%3A43%3A30 170w,/_gatsby/image/ee1800e39e88e194507dc0911c53faab/b2492daa83e9da8389f5d26273d1d994/How-to-Combine-Javascript-files-in-Magento-2-02.png?u=https%3A%2F%2Fwebguru.dev%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F03%2FHow-to-Combine-Javascript-files-in-Magento-2-02.png&a=w%3D339%26h%3D106%26fm%3Dpng%26q%3D90&cd=2023-03-10T04%3A43%3A30 339w,/_gatsby/image/ee1800e39e88e194507dc0911c53faab/21b33590a7bc7881a609788ba56181c3/How-to-Combine-Javascript-files-in-Magento-2-02.png?u=https%3A%2F%2Fwebguru.dev%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F03%2FHow-to-Combine-Javascript-files-in-Magento-2-02.png&a=w%3D678%26h%3D212%26fm%3Dpng%26q%3D90&cd=2023-03-10T04%3A43%3A30 678w\",\"sizes\":\"(min-width: 678px) 678px, 100vw\"}},\"layout\":\"constrained\",\"width\":678,\"height\":212},\"alt\":\"\",\"className\":\"wp-image-1205 inline-gatsby-image-wrapper\",\"data-wp-inline-image\":\"2\"}</script></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>This is where bundling comes in. When enabled, Magento 2 combines all RequireJS modules on-the-fly when the page is being rendered. Here&#8217;s how to enable bundling:</p>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>Log in to the Magento 2 Backend and go to Stores → Configuration → Advanced → Developer.</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Switch to the desired Storeview using the switcher on the top ribbon, if necessary. Bundling can also be enabled separately for each store.</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Expand the JS Settings section and enable the option to Enable JavaScript Bundling.</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Go to System → Cache Management, scroll to the Advanced Cache Management section, and press the Flush Javascript/CSS Cache button.</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Then, consecutively press the Flush Magento Cache and Flush Cache Storage buttons on the top ribbon.</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Regenerate the static content using the Flush Static Files Cache button in the Advanced Cache Management section.</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Unlike merging, bundling allows you to exclude Javascript modules from being combined. This is very useful when using modules with JS conflicts in combined mode.</li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<p>Excluding Javascript Modules from Bundling in Magento 2</p>\n\n\n\n<p>To exclude specific Javascript modules from the bundling process:</p>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>Log in to your store&#8217;s <a href=\"https://www.geeksforgeeks.org/difference-between-ftp-and-ssh/\">FTP/SSH</a> and go to the root of your store.</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Go to your theme directory (for example, the Luma theme is located at Magento root/vendor/Magento/theme-frontend-luma) and navigate to its, etc subdirectory.</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Open the view.xml file and locate the line &lt;vars module=&#8221;Js_Bundle&#8221;&gt;.</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Under this line, add the Javascript modules you want to exclude to the &lt;exclude&gt; block using the same naming as in the RequireJS loading directives.</li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<p>You can also adjust the bundle size of the dynamically created bundle by adjusting the bundle_size property.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Conclusion</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>In conclusion, <a href=\"/how-to-install-modules-manually-in-magento-2/\">installing modules manually in Magento 2</a> is a straightforward process that can greatly enhance your store&#8217;s functionality. If you&#8217;re looking to improve the performance of your Magento 2 website, combining Javascript files is a key step. By doing so, you can reduce the number of HTTP requests and improve page loading speed. When it comes to merging JS files, you can load a single large file instead of multiple separate modules, which can help optimize your website&#8217;s performance. However, it&#8217;s important to note that bundling is also necessary for files loaded via the RequireJS engine. By excluding certain JS modules from bundling, you can prevent conflicts and ensure that your website runs smoothly. By following the steps outlined in this guide on <strong><em>how to combine Javascript files in Magento 2</em></strong>, you can easily install modules and optimize your website&#8217;s performance.</p>\n<div class='sfsi_Sicons sfsi_Sicons_position_left' style='float: none; vertical-align: middle; text-align:left